However, he has noticed a new wave of people who have been influenced by the media&#39;s enthusiasm. People who have heard that records are back in vogue and have a need to buy back their old records.
Based on the conversations I&#39;ve had, people have gotten rid of their collection usually in 1998 or 1999.
Customers who sold their vinyl to buy CDs are now selling their CDs to buy their records back,” he says.
