Julius Nielsen from the University of Copenhagen and his colleagues found out.
He determined the ages of adult ice sharks from 28 females that had been caught by fishermen.
The age of the fish was revealed by radiocarbon dating of the eye lenses.
The average age of the studied sharks turned out to be at least 272 years.
