Another main reason for training a gun and explosives dog for Customs duties is mail shipments passing through Helsinki-Vantaa.
With the increased internet trade, up to 40 million mail items pass through the airport every year, among which may be weapons and explosives ordered from abroad.
In recent years, customs has made about 300 discoveries related to weapons, weapon parts, ammunition and explosives and their precursors at Helsinki-Vantaa airport among online shopping, passenger plane luggage and air cargo.
Heila will work in different parts of Helsinki-Vantaa.
It will examine checked baggage and mail.
In the future, it will be a big benefit in ports, when it can go through large container areas and mark areas that require a more detailed investigation, says Grönberg.
