Finnish research can help improve the effectiveness of cancer treatments
The recent research results of researchers at the University of Turku can help develop cancer treatments to be even more effective.
The findings of Academy Professor Johanna Ivaska&#39;s research group show that the hardness of a cancerous tumor increases the malignancy of the cancer.
Many human tissues, such as breast tissue, are very soft, and cells in the tissue grow normally in such an environment.
