A Square Meal: The Depressing Food of the Depression
In March 1933, shortly after becoming president, Franklin Delano Roosevelt sat down to lunch in his office.
A gourmet, President Roosevelt enjoyed sophisticated Fifth Avenue dishes such as foie gras and Maryland terrapin soup.
That day, her diet was more modest: stuffed eggs in tomato sauce, mashed potatoes and plum pudding for dessert.
